1. 飲茶  
廣東話：週日早晨，我哋一齊去飲茶，食咗蝦餃、叉燒包同埋腸粉，真係快人快事！  
English: On Sunday morning, we went for yum cha together, had shrimp dumplings, char siu buns and cheung fun — really a swift and satisfying experience!

2. 圖書館  
廣東話：我每日放學後都去圖書館溫書，因為度度都好安靜，可以集中精神讀書。  
English: I go to the library to study after school every day, because it’s always quiet and helps me focus.

3. 養聲  
廣東話：呢位歌手最近啱啱做完手術，要嚴格養聲，唔可以大聲講嘢或者唱歌。  
English: This singer just had surgery and now needs to carefully rest their voice, so they can’t speak loudly or sing.

4. 票尾  
廣東話：我買咗張電影票，但係唔使去，所以將票尾留低，日後可以當收據用。  
English: I bought a movie ticket but didn’t go, so I kept the stub as proof of purchase for later.

5. hacker  
廣東話：呢個公司被hacker入侵，好多客戶資料都外洩咗，真係好危險！  
English: This company got hacked, and lots of customer data was leaked — really dangerous!

6. 石斛蘭  
廣東話：我屋企窗台擺咗一盆石斛蘭，佢係依附喺木頭上面生長，好有自然美感。  
English: I’ve got a Dendrobium orchid on my windowsill; it grows by clinging to wood and looks very natural and beautiful.

7. 吊詭  
廣東話：明明佢最憎人講謊，但自己卻經常瞞住真相，真係好吊詭。  
English: He hates people lying, yet he’s always hiding the truth himself — such a contradiction.

8. 吊詭  
廣東話：呢個制度好似合理，但實際上卻令弱勢社群更難翻身，真係吊詭得來又荒謬。  
English: This system seems reasonable on paper, but in reality it makes it harder for the disadvantaged to rise — truly absurd and paradoxical.

9. 各為其主  
廣東話：雖然我哋以前係好兄弟，但而家各自為其主，我哋之間嘅關係就變得好複雜。  
English: Even though we used to be good friends, now we’re each serving our own masters, so our relationship has become very complicated.

10. 軨蓋  
廣東話：呢個軨蓋好重，我拎住都覺得好辛苦，你幫我一齊拎下啦。  
English: This hatch is so heavy, I’m struggling to carry it — help me lift it, will ya?

11. 打哥夫  
廣東話：我阿哥每逢週末都去打哥夫，鍛鍊身體又可以放鬆心情。  
English: My brother plays golf every weekend — it’s good exercise and helps him relax.

12. 免揀  
廣東話：呢間舖頭賣嘅電器都係免揀，唔使揀款式或者顏色，直接買就OK。  
English: All the electronics in this shop are non-selective — no need to choose style or colour, just buy and go.

13. 擺闊佬  
廣東話：佢新買咗部超豪華車，仲成日開去酒樓食飯，真係擺闊佬到極致！  
English: He just bought a super-luxury car and keeps driving to restaurants every day — really showing off his wealth!

14. 廣播劇  
廣東話：我最鍾意聽廣播劇，尤其係深夜時分，一邊瞓一邊聽，好有感覺。  
English: I love listening to radio dramas, especially late at night — it feels so immersive while I’m half-asleep.

15. 錄影機  
廣東話：我媽咪買咗部新錄影機，準備將我哋全家旅行嘅片段全部錄低。  
English: My mum bought a new video recorder to tape all our family holiday moments.

16. 吟詩吟唔甩  
廣東話：警方已經有證據，佢偷咗我哋公司嘅資料，真係吟詩吟唔甩，唔使再辯啦。  
English: The police already have solid evidence — he stole our company’s data, so it’s undeniable; no point arguing anymore.

17. 佈道大會  
廣東話：上個禮拜日，教堂舉行咗一場大型佈道大會，好多人都去參加，場面好熱鬧。  
English: Last Sunday, the church held a big evangelism meeting — lots of people attended, and it was very lively.

18. 寫手  
廣東話：呢位寫手文筆好犀利，寫嘅文章讀完之後令人深思。  
English: This writer has sharp prose — reading their articles makes you reflect deeply.

19. 寫手  
廣東話：我哋公司請咗一位寫手，幫我哋撰寫廣告文案，效果好到爆。  
English: Our company hired a ghostwriter to write our ad copy, and it’s been super effective.

20. 代打  
廣東話：我今日有事，唔可以玩遊戲，你可唔可以代打我？  
English: I’ve got something to do today and can’t play the game — can you play for me?

21. 茶碗  
廣東話：呢個茶碗係日本茶道用嘅，陶瓷製成，好有質感，我好鍾意。  
English: This tea bowl is used in Japanese tea ceremonies, made of ceramic with great texture — I really love it.

22. 茶隔  
廣東話：煮茶時要用茶隔，將茶葉同茶湯分開，先至可以斟出好飲嘅茶。  
English: When brewing tea, you must use a tea strainer to separate the leaves from the liquid, so you can pour a good-tasting brew.

23. 只許州官放火，不准百姓點燈  
廣東話：公司老闆自己遲到都唔使負責，但員工遲到就要罰錢，真係只許州官放火，唔準百姓點燈！  
English: The boss can be late without consequences, but employees get fined for being late — classic case of “only the official can set fire, but commoners can’t light a lamp!”

24. 獨唱  
廣東話：今晚演唱會，佢要獨唱一首歌，我好期待佢表現！  
English: Tonight’s concert, he’s doing a solo performance — I’m really looking forward to how he’ll do!

25. 快人快事  
廣東話：我哋一拍即合，即刻決定去旅行，真係快人快事！  
English: We agreed instantly and decided to go on a trip right away — truly a swift and satisfying decision!

26. 四腳獸  
廣東話：我上廁所時，見到門縫有四隻腳，原來係兩個人喺度親熱，真係四腳獸！  
English: When I went to the toilet, I saw four legs through the door crack — turns out two people were making out inside, real “four-legged beasts”!

27. 無米粥  
廣東話：呢個合作計劃仲未定好細節，我哋先講講無米粥，唔好期望太高。  
English: The cooperation plan isn’t finalised yet — let’s just talk about “riceless porridge” for now, don’t get your hopes up.

28. 義會  
廣東話：我哋鄰居一齊組咗個義會，有需要時可以借錢，仲可以分紅，好實際。  
English: My neighbours formed a mutual aid society — we can borrow money when needed and even share profits; very practical.

29. 榜文  
廣東話：官府貼出榜文，宣布新法例，市民都要睇清楚。  
English: The government posted a notice on the bulletin board announcing a new law — citizens must read it carefully.

30. MK名  
廣東話：佢個MK名係「醉愛@星河夢幻」，好有特色，一睇就知係網上人。  
English: His online nickname is “醉愛@星河夢幻” — very distinctive, you can tell he’s an internet user at a glance. [end of text]


